Chief of Human Capital of Maximus (NYSE:MMS), Andrekovich Mark, sells 8,939 shares worth $572,185
According to Maximus's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated Jun 13 10:55 AM, company Chief of Human Capital, Andrekovich Mark disclosed selling 8,939 shares at a cost of $64.01. At the time of this transaction (Jun 09), this trade was worth $572,185 in total. As of Jun 09, Andrekovich Mark now owns 24,583 shares in total worth about $1,575,032.81. 
For the last few recent trades made by Maximus (NYSE:MMS) Chief of Human Capital, Andrekovich Mark, we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: Feb 21: Sold 5,620 shares at the rate of $58.86 per share. Total worth of this trade was $330,819. Total number of shares owned as of Feb 21 were 33,522
SEC Form 4 filing: Dec 15: Sold 2,455 shares at the rate of $54.87 per share. Total worth of this trade was $134,706. Total number of shares owned as of Dec 15 were 39,513
SEC Form 4 filing: Mar 03: Sold 3,722 shares at the rate of $60.00 per share. Total worth of this trade was $223,320. Total number of shares owned as of Mar 03 were 18,820




